    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pollock-pea-and-sweet-potato-casserole/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a knob of<strong> butter</strong> over a medium heat</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pollock-pea-and-sweet-potato-casserole/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small, rough pieces</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife, then remove the skin</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pollock-pea-and-sweet-potato-casserole/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>to the dish and cook for 30 secs</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pollock-pea-and-sweet-potato-casserole/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>crushed garlic</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good stir and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pollock-pea-and-sweet-potato-casserole/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely and set aside for serving</p><p>Once boiling, cover the casserole dish with a lid and put it in the oven for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are tender</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pollock-pea-and-sweet-potato-casserole/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, remove the dish from the oven and add your <strong>blanched peas</strong></p><p>Give everything a good stir, then top with your <strong>diced pollock </strong>(unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!)</p><p>Return the dish to the oven, uncovered, for 7-8 min or until the pollock is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pollock-pea-and-sweet-potato-casserole/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, stir your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong> through the sauce and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>one pot creamy pollock</strong>,<strong> pea & potato casserole</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong> and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
